So, one of the weirdest things to fully get my head around about fascism is the "the enemy is weak/the enemy is strong" dichotomy, how people caught in the fascist delusion must simultaneously believe two contradictory things about the scapegoat - the first, that the scapegoat is too weak or "wrong" to properly contribute to society, but also the scapegoat is so strong that their very existence is enough to bring society crashing down.

But then, when everyone (meaning mainstream media) was talking about how "surprising" it was that Hamas surprised security folks with their attacks on Oct 7 I got to see it in action. How did Hamas - a weak little extremist terrorist group - get around Israel's security? Well, we must now bomb Gaza to smithereens killing thousands and thousands of innocent people, because Hamas is too powerful to let exist.

I just saw someone complaining about the ‚Äúpetty drama‚Äù of block lists. If you think it‚Äôs ‚Äúpetty‚Äù, then either (a) you‚Äôre not seeing the harassment, or (b) you approve of the harassment. The harassment is real, and there‚Äôs nothing petty about wanting to exist peacefully on social media without being harassed and trolled.

There are lots of reasons why privileged white people don‚Äôt see the harassment. We choose who to follow, so if we don‚Äôt follow garbage, then we don‚Äôt see it. POC users, on the other hand, also don‚Äôt follow garbage, but the garbage seeks them out and jumps into their mentions. And there are gross tricks like replying with your post visible to followers only, so only the target and the other garbage-following trash see it.
Or maybe you saw your POC friend‚Äôs post, and you favorited it and moved on. Maybe you didn‚Äôt come back two hours later to see the pile-on of gross replies.

Dice rolls are the bread and butter to almost every mechanic. They have the form xdy+z, where x is the number of dice, y is the number of die sides, and z is a flat modifier to add/subtract.

For example, "3d4+6" means to roll 3, 4 sided dice, sum the result, and add 6.

Some "rolls" are constants, e.g. "4", in which case the number 4 is always used.

Keeping my hair vivid/rainbow shades is a really big gender expression thing for me, so while it's obviously not ill willed it has been a bit dysphoria-inducing that every year around halloween random strangers stop me to say things like ‚Äúwhat costume is your hair *current color* for?‚Äù or ‚ÄúWow that color is still really bright, it‚Äôs been weeks since Halloween! Did you use real dye or is that from the spray?‚Äù or the admittedly hilarious time a few years ago a woman stopped me and my wife in the grocery store in early October clearly thinking we were like high schoolers and said ‚Äúwow are the schools really letting you kids come in with your hair like that this far before Halloween now?‚Äù and I had to as politely as possible be like ‚Äúhaha well this isn‚Äôt for Halloween my hair is colorful year round, and I‚Äôm not sure what school rules are like for hair these days, I‚Äôm actually 26.‚Äù

But but but! Today for the very first time (and just a week before Halloween!) I had someone not only not assume my hair was colorful for halloween but without asking/knowing assume it was NOT!

My hair is currently blue (I change colors roughly every month) and today when I was getting some medical tests done the nurse I was working with excitedly asked "Oh, are you gonna dye your hair ORANGE for halloween?" in a way that was very clearly meant as 'well this is obviously your normal hair, are you doing any halloween hair?' and damn that gave me a rush of gender euphoria.

It was such a little moment, but I gotta admit really needed that today.

#Trans #Nonbinary #Enby #TransJoy #EnbyJoy #NonbinaryJoy #GenderEuphoria
